txt.en: Bakhíl can be found somewhere inside Utterby.\n\nYou should challenge and defeat Bakhíl.
Kunchat is pleased with your prowess in duels.\n\nYou should talk to Kunchat.
Kunchat has heard of your victory and wishes to speak with you.\n\nYou should talk to Kunchat.
Kunchat has heard of your victory and wishes to speak with you.\n\nYou should talk to Kunchat.

'Ah, here is my busy little Chayasír. I hear more good things from Yólkhon. How would you like to climb the ladder higher? Go find Sháwat and challenge him. I do not think he will be much trouble for you.'
'A Chayasír weakling challenges me? I will break your bones!'

'Chayasír, Otkóz tells me you have helped us prepare Er Shamol for an attack. This is good. We should be able to hold off the dwarves now. As a reward for your hard work, I will tell you the name of the Man you must defeat next: Bakhíl. He is known to be dishonourable in duels, so consider yourself warned! I would hate to lose my pet Chayasír now.'
'A challenger? Good, I was growing bored!'
'Haha! Chayasír, I am impressed! I will spread word of your triumphs!'
The Jangovar climb ranks by beating their betters in combat. Perhaps if you are able to defeat some of them yourself, the Jangovar will look upon you favourably.
'You Chayasír need to learn your place!'

'Kúlkhur tells me you did the tasks you were given without complaint. That is a good start, but how would you like to separate yourself from the rest of the weaklings here? Jangovar prove themselves by defeating their betters in combat. Then they become the betters. If you succeed and climb the ranks, perhaps Akh-gulûkh will notice you. But you must start at the bottom rung of the ladder. Find Jáldor, and challenge him to a duel. If you succeed, perhaps some less menial tasks will open up for you. The duels are not meant to be to the death, but, accidents happen....'\n\nHe laughs cruelly.
'You wish to challenge me, Chayasír? You will end up dead, fool!'
'Good, good! Jáldor was a fool, and I am glad to be rid of him. Report to Yólkhon. If you can complete his tasks, I may tell you who next you can challenge.'
'You surprise me, Chayasír. I did not know your kind had such martial prowess. Report to Otkóz now. He will have more work for you.'
Kunchat may let you challenge another Jangovar leader as you earn his favour.\n\nYou should complete more quests in Utterby.
